  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Depot Surveyor",
  "description": "<p><u><strong>PURPOSE</strong></u></p><ul><li>Surveyors is to ensure all ISO Tank Containers turned into our depot are surveyed, cleaned and  repaired to the customers requirement standard criteria comply to ITCO/ACC or owner criteria.</li></ul><p><br /></p><p><u><strong>SCOPE</strong></u></p><ul><li>Surveyors is to ensure all ISO Tank Containers that have been accepted by MW Tank Depot.</li></ul><p><br /></p><p><u><strong>RESPONSIBILITY</strong></u></p><ul><li>Surveyors is to ensure that all ISO Tank Containers turned into our depot must conduct surveyed.</li><li>Surveyors’  responsibility for all the ISO tank containers turn into depot are thoroughly survey correctly and to ensure the documents are endorsed before issued the Equipment.</li></ul><p><br /></p><p><u><strong>JOB DESCRIPTION</strong></u></p><ul><li>All ISO tank containers turn into depot, surveyors ensure to stick a yellow and red colour.</li><li>Sticker onto the Left-Hand Side of the corner post before off load.</li><li>Surveyors must coordinate with the Leese/Lessor independent surveyor for joint inspection.</li><li>As part of a Surveyors duties, ensure to conduct thorough inspection after the cleaning, repaired and testing completed.</li><li>Surveyors must thoroughly inspect the Tank Containers and raised estimates after the cleaning completed.</li><li>Surveyors must report to the supervisor on all documentation of ISO Tank containers before sending to customers.</li><li>Surveyors will conduct Pre/Post inspection, if require by Customers (Before Repair and After Repaired).</li><li>As a surveyors must obtain instruction from the Supervisor.</li><li>Surveyors must inform the Side Lifter Drivers to shift the Tank Containers into the workshop area for repair when Customers given the approval to repair.</li><li>Surveyors must hand over the approved estimates to the Repairer Supervisor after the tank containers shifted into the repair bay.</li><li>Surveyors ensure the repairer repair items accordingly indicated on the estimates and repair standard complies to ITCO/ACC or Owner criteria.</li></ul>",
